MOST IMPORTANT
Correlate the phrase in Isaiah with the cross reference in Revelation, as instructed.
Arise, shine; for thy light is come, and the glory of the LORD is risen upon thee... and his glory shall be seen upon thee.|Revelation 21:11
And the Gentiles shall come to thy light, and kings to the brightness of thy rising.|Revelation 21:24, 26
... the forces of the Gentiles shall come unto thee.|Revelation 21:24, 26
...that men may bring unto thee the forces of the Gentiles, and that their kings may be brought.|Revelation 21:24, 26
Therefore thy gates shall be open continually; they shall not be shut day nor night;|Revelation 21:25
For the nation and kingdom that will not serve thee shall perish; yea, those nations shall be utterly wasted.|Revelation 21:8
...The city of the LORD, The Zion of the Holy One of Israel.|Revelation 21:2, 10
Violence shall no more be heard in thy land, wasting nor destruction within thy borders;|Revelation 22:3
but thou shalt call thy walls Salvation, and thy gates Praise. |Revelation 21:14, 21
The sun shall be no more thy light by day; neither for brightness shall the moon give light unto thee: but the LORD shall be unto thee an everlasting light, and thy God thy glory...|Revelation 21:23
... and the days of thy mourning shall be ended.|Revelation 21:4
Thy people also shall be all righteous...|Revelation 21:27

SECOND MOST IMPORTANT (This will help you learn the verses faster)
Know the content of the marked verses in Revelation. Emphasis is on the highlighted section.
The glory of God:|Revelation 21:11
Glory and honour of all the nations|Revelation 21:24, 26
The gates shall not be shut for there shall be no night there.|Revelation 21:25
Those who do not serve God will be in the lake of fire.|Revelation 21:8
The city is coming from God.|Revelation 21:2, 10
There will be no more curse.|Revelation 22:3
The gates and walls of the city.|Revelation 21:14, 21
No need of the sun or moon.|Revelation 21:23
No more death, sorrow, crying, or pain.|Revelation 21:4
There shall no thing that defileth enter in.|Revelation 21:27

