Not sure about this one either. Correlating the reference in Isaiah to what it says.
Isaiah 60:1-2|Arise, shine; for thy light is come, and the glory of the LORD is risen upon thee... and his glory shall be seen upon thee.
Isaiah 60:3|And the Gentiles shall come to thy light, and kings to the brightness of thy rising.
Isaiah 60:5|... the forces of the Gentiles shall come unto thee.
Isaiah 60:11b|...that men may bring unto thee the forces of the Gentiles, and that their kings may be brought.
Isaiah 60:11a|Therefore thy gates shall be open continually; they shall not be shut day nor night;
Isaiah 60:12|For the nation and kingdom that will not serve thee shall perish; yea, those nations shall be utterly wasted.
Isaiah 60:14|...The city of the LORD, The Zion of the Holy One of Israel.
Isaiah 60:18a|Violence shall no more be heard in thy land, wasting nor destruction within thy borders;
Isaiah 60:18b|but thou shalt call thy walls Salvation, and thy gates Praise. 
Isaiah 60:19|The sun shall be no more thy light by day; neither for brightness shall the moon give light unto thee: but the LORD shall be unto thee an everlasting light, and thy God thy glory...
Isaiah 60:20|... and the days of thy mourning shall be ended.
Isaiah 60:21|Thy people also shall be all righteous...